---
description: DTO, schema, and mapping rules
globs: ["src/**/*", "src-tauri/src/**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

All cross-layer communication must use explicit DTOs.

Rules:
- do not expose raw infrastructure models directly to the UI
- do not pass untyped JSON between layers
- define DTOs for Tauri command input/output
- validate external/untrusted payloads
- map infrastructure models to DTOs explicitly
- map DTOs to UI/domain models explicitly when useful

Frontend:
- use zod for runtime validation where external payloads enter the app
- keep API/DTO types separate from view-model types when needed

Backend:
- use serde serialize/deserialize structs consistently
- keep command input/output structs stable and intentional
- do not leak parser-only fields into public contracts

Mapping rules:
- parsers -> infrastructure models
- infrastructure models -> DTOs
- DTOs -> feature/entity view models

Do not skip mapping if it weakens boundaries or leaks implementation details.